 <br>
Hello!<br>
 <br>
 I don't know if this is the right place to send this, but I hope you can get this message to the people who can do something about it.<br>
 <br>
 Many players in DAoC now use a secondary account for the purpose of creating a character to enhance their primary account. This would be fine if both accounts are played but many are just using the second account to &quot;buff&quot; their first character then sit in a portal keep safely away from harm.<br>
 <br>
 Impact on the game is three fold..<br>
  <br>
  First the players that do not &quot;buff bot&quot; meet a super human character on the battlefield and are promptly killed. They then complain about how powerful xxx class is to customer support and on boards around the Internet. <br>
 <br>
 Second impact is some players who worked hard on their characters that are killed by &quot;buff botted&quot; supermen loose interest in the game since they can see no way to compete with this. They blame mythic for it, and move on to other games mainly because they could not compete with all the &quot;buff botted&quot; supermen showing up in rvr. <br>
 <br>
 Third impact is that more and more people that create the support classes that are used for buff bots, find that they are not needed in rvr as much as they should be because they did not spec high enough in buffing to do a better job than the bott. most of the support classes don't have a lot of offense ability so they go into healing as their only true choice to be of value in rvr and feel trapped into doing so.<br>
 <br>
 Solutions..<br>
 <br>
 I have thought on this for over 2 weeks. I cant see any reason why people should not be able to do buff bots. It's their money and they are paying to play the game. I also don't think reducing the effect of buffs will help.. since no mater how much they are reduced, the ones with buff bots will still hold that edge over the rest, no matter how small. Where the issue is really hurting the game is in rvr, so that is the main focus for this fix.<br>
 <br>
 *** In the portal keeps place an NPC &quot;Sister Julie&quot; that is available to cast buffs on anyone who is willing to &quot;donate&quot; a small tithe of 5gp or so, for 30 min of buffs. (Not concentration based but timer based so she don't have to worry about a concentration pool) <br>
Buffs cast for the donation should be ..baseline AF ..baseline Dex ..baseline Con ..baseline Str ..specline Str/Con ..specline Dex/Qui ..specline AF ***<br>
 <br>
 The impact this will have is that of leveling the playing field for all players who wish to RvR. It does not nerf the buff bot players since their buffs are longer concentration based and free.<br>
 <br>
 As for the three problems.. the first one where you meet a superman that kills you will not be so common, if you get your buffs before going out. And rvr combat will last longer which is what many people were looking for.<br>
<br>
  The second one where people who worked hard on their character are leaving.. they may leave but it will not be because some buffed superman was bullying them around on their server. They will have the same ability to buff up for rvr and go out with their classes strengths and see what they can do.<br>
 <br>
 The third problem of support classes being trapped into healing roles in rvr.. don't really change. Sad but for support classes this solution will not make specializing in &quot;part buffs and part something else&quot; any more useful than before. It will allow them more time to heal their group though, since the members will have more hit points and be tougher to take down.<br>
 <br>
 Sorry about any spelling errors, I hope this made sense?<br>
 <br>
 Thanks for reading!<br>
